[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care-coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-system data integration as architectural primitive.** The assistant reads across the institution's full data landscape. Each integration is engineered with appropriate identity-resolution, consent enforcement, retry handling, and data-quality flagging. Integration outages degrade gracefully without breaking the conversation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-pathway-as-code with clinical-leadership ownership.** The pathway library is owned by clinical leadership, version-controlled, reviewed annually, and re-reviewed on material updates. Each pathway has defined milestones, expected timelines, escalation criteria, and education touchpoints.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Pending-action ledger with closed-loop discipline.** Every action initiated for the patient is tracked from initiation through completion. Items aging past institutional thresholds escalate; items completing close and log.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-provider conflict flagging.** When providers' recommendations conflict, the assistant surfaces the conflict and routes resolution; it does not adjudicate.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Equity-focused per-cohort monitoring.** Engagement, attrition, closed-loop rates, escalation rates, and outcome measures are monitored per language, channel, condition, age cohort, sex, social-determinant flags, geographic region, and plan type. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by clinical leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When integration sources are unreachable, the assistant degrades gracefully. Crisis-pathway integrity is preserved across all degraded states.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
